<paragraph blockId="5.[151,684,385,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">
<taxonomicName box="[177,375,385,412]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sarcolaenaceae" genus="Xyloolaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Huerteales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis box="[177,375,385,412]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Xyloolaena perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a tree c. 
<quantity box="[506,588,385,412]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="7.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="4.0">4-10 m</quantity>
tall that has been recorded at scattered localities from near Morondava, Ankarafantsika PN and the Lokia [=Loky] river basin E of Ambilobe (Fig. 1) within Madagascar’s dry bioclimatic region. Although the known populations are widely disjunct, it may be that this species is more continuously distributed (but bridging the humid Sambirano region) and has simply not yet been recorded from the intervening areas, large parts of which remain under-explored. 
<taxonomicName box="[414,609,692,719]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sarcolaenaceae" genus="Xyloolaena" kingdom="Plantae" order="Huerteales" pageId="5" pageNumber="12" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perrieri">
<emphasis box="[414,609,692,719]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">Xyloolaena perrieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other members of the genus by having erect, cup-shaped red flowers borne in pairs within the involucre, and leaves with bullate blades in which the secondary veins are strongly impressed on the upper surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,684,385,1087]" box="[177,525,876,903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="12">VERNACULAR NAME. — Zahana.</paragraph>
